The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festival Festa Academica offers for the third time the festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The festival nail consists of two concerts organized on 17 November.
Charles University has an important part in this festival.
"Among the choirs is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," said the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The festival nail is the Choeur concert of high schools and secondary classes that takes place with free entry on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening there is the concert "Students of velvet" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the upper schools as well as that of Charles University occur.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Students' Day and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Treasures in cooperation with high school Jan Kepler.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, musical meetings, student learning and other activities.
Interested people will find all information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
